CHROME RACER brushed out a but at the start, tried to match strides with the leader early on, settled for second tier in between horses down the backside, hooked with other foe in the turn battled down the lane and out lasted the others while securing second. SHE'S MY LOUIE V. hopped at start, raced in the second tier from the inside, had aim on the leader through the turn, hooked another foe down the lane, battled with that foe for the place spot, but didn't have enough and was able to show . ZIGGZAPPA settled early, was moved out from behind horses down the back side, saved ground through the turn was asked down the lane but didn't have enough. SUNDAY HOUSE was placed in the second tier down the backside, showed brief run moving into the turn, flattened out coming out of the turn, came down the lane and and switched leads back and forth with no finish.
